This update for openvswitch fixes the following issues:

- CVE-2023-5366: Fixed missing masks on a final stage with ports trie (bsc#1216002).

notes.text: A flaw was found in Open vSwitch that allows ICMPv6 Neighbor Advertisement packets between virtual machines to bypass OpenFlow rules. This issue may allow a local attacker to create specially crafted packets with a modified or spoofed target IP address field that can redirect ICMPv6 traffic to arbitrary IP addresses.
